dSigma","link":"./../semantic/307601613138768701.xml#","docLink":"./Init/NotationExtra.html#unexpandSigma","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/NotationExtra.lean#L148-L150","name":"unexpandPSigma","link":"./../semantic/11122186495135363113.xml#","docLink":"./Init/NotationExtra.html#unexpandPSigma","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/NotationExtra.lean#L152-L155","name":"unexpandSubtype","link":"./../semantic/12120920806386129877.xml#","docLink":"./Init/NotationExtra.html#unexpandSubtype","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/NotationExtra.lean#L157-L170","name":"tacticFunext__","link":"./../semantic/10752776619736283999.xml#","docLink":"./Init/NotationExtra.html#tacticFunext__","doc":"Apply function extensionality and introduce new hypotheses.\nThe tactic `funext` will keep applying new the `funext` lemma until the goal target is not reducible to\n```\n  |-  ((fun x => ...) = (fun x => ...))\n```\nThe variant `funext h₁ ... hₙ` applies `funext` `n` times, and uses the given identifiers to name the new hypotheses.\nPatterns can be used like in the `intro` tactic. Example, given a goal\n```\n  |-  ((fun x : Nat × Bool => ...) = (fun x => ...))\n```\n`funext (a, b)` applies `funext` once and performs pattern matching on the newly introduced pair.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/NotationExtra.lean#L202-L203","name":"«command_ClassAbbrev__:_:=__,»","link":"./../semantic/10953572748141975661.xml#","docLink":"./Init/NotationExtra.html#«command_ClassAbbrev__:_:=__,»","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/NotationExtra.lean#L212-L213","name":"«tactic·.__;_»","link":"./../semantic/2963983179174740133.xml#","docLink":"./Init/NotationExtra.html#«tactic·.__;_»","doc":"`· tac` focuses on the main goal and tries to solve it using `tac`, or else fails. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/NotationExtra.lean#L217-L220","name":"solve","link":"./../semantic/6747941676885523753.xml#","docLink":"./Init/NotationExtra.html#solve","doc":"Similar to `first`, but succeeds only if one the given tactics solves the current goal.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/NotationExtra.lean#L228-L229","name":"Lean.Loop","link":"./../semantic/14173235586246573429.xml#","docLink":"./Init/NotationExtra.html#Lean.Loop","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/NotationExtra.lean#L232-L237","name":"Lean.Loop.forIn","link":"./../semantic/10354851540704571879.xml#","docLink":"./Init/NotationExtra.html#Lean.Loop.forIn","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/NotationExtra.lean#L233-L236","name":"Lean.Loop.forIn.loop","link":"./../semantic/5513021119741176813.xml#","docLink":"./Init/NotationExtra.html#Lean.Loop.forIn.loop","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/NotationExtra.lean#L239-L240","name":"Lean.instForInLoopUnit","link":"./../semantic/14508542580485902473.xml#","docLink":"./Init/NotationExtra.html#Lean.instForInLoopUnit","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/NotationExtra.lean#L242-L242","name":"Lean.doElemRepeat_","link":"./../semantic/13587845211119840877.xml#","docLink":"./Init/NotationExtra.html#Lean.doElemRepeat_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/N