0/LeanColls/Queue.lean#L13-L16","name":"LeanColls.Queue","link":"./../semantic/2475027349963846215.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Queue.html#LeanColls.Queue","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Queue.lean#L20-L24","name":"LeanColls.Queue.CorrectFIFO","link":"./../semantic/6657397779257487647.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Queue.html#LeanColls.Queue.CorrectFIFO","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Queue.lean#L26-L30","name":"LeanColls.Queue.CorrectLIFO","link":"./../semantic/5864334968351727209.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Queue.html#LeanColls.Queue.CorrectLIFO","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Data/Option/Instances.lean#L11-L15","name":"Option.eq_of_eq_some","link":"./../semantic/2318440185430542085.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Data/Option/Instances.html#Option.eq_of_eq_some","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Data/Option/Instances.lean#L17-L18","name":"Option.eq_none_of_isNone","link":"./../semantic/8198969082875367015.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Data/Option/Instances.html#Option.eq_none_of_isNone","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L12-L13","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.withAnnotateState","link":"./../semantic/7168602213025936229.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.withAnnotateState","doc":"`with_annotate_state stx t` annotates the lexical range of `stx : Syntax` with the initial and final state of running tactic `t`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L15-L33","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.intro","link":"./../semantic/17402865129139278309.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.intro","doc":"Introduce one or more hypotheses, optionally naming and/or pattern-matching them.\nFor each hypothesis to be introduced, the remaining main goal's target type must be a `let` or function type.\n* `intro` by itself introduces one anonymous hypothesis, which can be accessed by e.g. `assumption`.\n* `intro x y` introduces two hypotheses and names them. Individual hypotheses can be anonymized via `_`,\n  or matched against a pattern:\n  ```lean\n  -- ... ⊢ α × β → ...\n  intro (a, b)\n  -- ..., a : α, b : β ⊢ ...\n  ```\n* Alternatively, `intro` can be combined with pattern matching much like `fun`:\n  ```lean\n  intro\n  | n + 1, 0 => tac\n  | ...\n  ```\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L34-L35","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.intros","link":"./../semantic/14221804682197426433.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.intros","doc":"`intros x...` behaves like `intro x...`, but then keeps introducing (anonymous) hypotheses until goal is not of a function type. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L36-L39","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.rename","link":"./../semantic/4475571077697689127.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.rename","doc":"`rename t => x` renames the most recent hypothesis whose type matches `t` (which may contain placeholders) to `x`,\nor fails if no such hypothesis could be found. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L40-L41","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.revert","link":"./../semantic/6633503797509847769.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.revert","doc":"`revert x...` is the inverse of `intro x...`: it moves the given hypotheses into the main goal's target type. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L42-L43","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.clear","link":"./../semantic/4788007406659257775.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.clear","doc":"`clear x...` removes the given hypotheses, or fails if there are remaining references to a hypothesis. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L44-L47","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.subst","link":"./../semantic/10886185670068869033.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.subst","doc":"`subst x...` substitutes each `x` with `e` in the goal if there is a hypothesis of type `x = e` or `e = x`.\nIf `x` is itself a hypothesis of type `y = e` or `e = y`, `y` is substituted instead. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L48-L51","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.assumption","link":"./../semantic/5471390806776695527.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.assumption","doc":"`assumption` tries to solve the main goal using a hypothesis of compatible type, or else fails.\nNote also the `‹t›` term notation, which is a shorthand for `show t by assumption`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L52-L75","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.contradiction","link":"./../semantic/4710949832259743233.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.contradiction","doc":"`contradiction` closes the main goal if its hypotheses are \"trivially contradictory\".\n- Inductive type/family with no applicable constructors\n```lean\nexample (h : False) : p := by contradiction\n```\n- Injectivity of constructors\n```lean\nexample (h : none = some true) : p := by contradiction  --\n```\n- Decidable false proposition\n```lean\nexample (h : 2 + 2 = 3) : p := by contradiction\n```\n- Contradictory hypotheses\n```lean\nexample (h : p) (h' : ¬ p) : q := by contradiction\n```\n- Other simple contradictions such as\n```lean\nexample (x : Nat) (h : x ≠ x) : p := by contradiction\n```\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L76-L84","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.apply","link":"./../semantic/10233995239623531853.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.apply","doc":"`apply e` tries to match the current goal against the conclusion of `e`'s type.\nIf it succeeds, then the tactic returns as many subgoals as the number of premises that\nhave not been fixed by type inference or type class resolution.\nNon-dependent premises are added before dependent ones.\n\nThe `apply` tactic uses higher-order pattern matching, type class resolution, and first-order unification with dependent types.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L85-L88","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.exact","link":"./../semantic/12613814261787041117.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.exact","doc":"`exact e` closes the main goal if its target type matches that of `e`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L89-L93","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.refine","link":"./../semantic/17522448694755385543.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.refine","doc":"`refine e` behaves like `exact e`, except that named (`?x`) or unnamed (`?_`) holes in `e` that are not solved\nby unification with the main goal's target type are converted into new goals, using the hole's name, if any, as the goal case name.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L94-L95","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.refine'","link":"./../semantic/842689916303204677.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.refine'","doc":"`refine' e` behaves like `refine e`, except that unsolved placeholders (`_`) and implicit parameters are also converted into new goals. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L96-L97","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.constructor","link":"./../semantic/15599055256032349579.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.constructor","doc":"If the main goal's target type is an inductive type, `constructor` solves it with the first matching constructor, or else fails. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L98-L101","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.case","link":"./../semantic/6053691362389903795.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.case","doc":"`case tag => tac` focuses on the goal with case name `tag` and solves it using `tac`, or else fails.\n`case tag x₁ ... xₙ => tac` additionally renames the `n` most recent hypotheses with inaccessible names to the given names. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L102-L107","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.case'","link":"./../semantic/3670625575391837757.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.case'","doc":"`case'` is similar to the `case tag => tac` tactic, but does not ensure the goal has been solved after applying `tac`, nor\nadmits the goal if `tac` failed. Recall that `case` closes the goal using `sorry` when `tac` fails, and\nthe tactic execution is not interrupted.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L109-L112","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tacticNext___=>_»","link":"./../semantic/10640352880538208211.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tacticNext___=>_»","doc":"`next => tac` focuses on the next goal solves it using `tac`, or else fails.\n`next x₁ ... xₙ => tac` additionally renames the `n` most recent hypotheses with inaccessible names to the given names. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L114-L115","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.allGoals","link":"./../semantic/6145825727778322419.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.allGoals","doc":"`all_goals tac` runs `tac` on each goal, concatenating the resulting goals, if any. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L116-L117","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.anyGoals","link":"./../semantic/15174319498215257985.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.anyGoals","doc":"`any_goals tac` applies the tactic `tac` to every goal, and succeeds if at least one application succeeds.  "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L118-L121","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.focus","link":"./../semantic/7130736660569328821.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.focus","doc":"`focus tac` focuses on the main goal, suppressing all other goals, and runs `tac` on it.\nUsually `· tac`, which enforces that the goal is closed by `tac`, should be preferred. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L122-L123","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.skip","link":"./../semantic/16848977032227284721.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.skip","doc":"`skip` does nothing. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L124-L125","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.done","link":"./../semantic/14155599149755222065.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.done","doc":"`done` succeeds iff there are no remaining goals. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L126-L127","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.traceState","link":"./../semantic/17122479126477242025.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.traceState","doc":"`trace_state` displays the current state in the info view. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L128-L129","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.traceMessage","link":"./../semantic/943287481980766047.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.traceMessage","doc":"`trace msg` displays `msg` in the info view. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L130-L131","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.failIfSuccess","link":"./../semantic/10275941755935439003.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.failIfSuccess","doc":"`fail_if_success t` fails if the tactic `t` succeeds. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L132-L132","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.paren","link":"./../semantic/17393560597314129521.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.paren","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L133-L133","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.withReducible","link":"./../semantic/15263123838593183357.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.withReducible","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L134-L134","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.withReducibleAndInstances","link":"./../semantic/13722797373677586123.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.withReducibleAndInstances","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L135-L135","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.withUnfoldingAll","link":"./../semantic/15914807842092682903.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.withUnfoldingAll","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L136-L137","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.first","link":"./../semantic/427876026619100709.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.first","doc":"`first | tac | ...` runs each `tac` until one succeeds, or else fails. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L138-L138","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.rotateLeft","link":"./../semantic/7345352141083943007.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.rotateLeft","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L139-L139","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.rotateRight","link":"./../semantic/17140577128441892545.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.rotateRight","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L140-L141","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticTry_","link":"./../semantic/14262516925126399471.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticTry_","doc":"`try tac` runs `tac` and succeeds even if `tac` failed. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L142-L143","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tactic_<;>_»","link":"./../semantic/16473879056817549341.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tactic_<;>_»","doc":"`tac <;> tac'` runs `tac` on the main goal and `tac'` on each produced goal, concatenating all goals produced by `tac'`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L150-L151","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.refl","link":"./../semantic/10145923012883883283.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.refl","doc":"`eq_refl` is equivalent to `exact rfl`, but has a few optimizations. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L153-L158","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticRfl","link":"./../semantic/900050247022513773.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticRfl","doc":"`rfl` tries to close the current goal using reflexivity.\nThis is supposed to be an extensible tactic and users can add their own support\nfor new reflexive relations.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L160-L163","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticRfl'","link":"./../semantic/2010723927212462771.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticRfl'","doc":"`rfl'` is similar to `rfl`, but disables smart unfolding and unfolds all kinds of definitions,\n  theorems included (relevant for declarations defined by well-founded recursion). "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L165-L165","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.ac_refl","link":"./../semantic/17226987681479671357.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.ac_refl","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L167-L168","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticAdmit","link":"./../semantic/6978892680042399241.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticAdmit","doc":"`admit` is a shorthand for `exact sorry`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L169-L170","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticSorry","link":"./../semantic/12972049151286018015.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticSorry","doc":"The `sorry` tactic is a shorthand for `exact sorry`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L171-L172","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticInfer_instance","link":"./../semantic/10417222844760313453.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticInfer_instance","doc":"`infer_instance` is an abbreviation for `exact inferInstance` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L174-L175","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.config","link":"./../semantic/3140477293059881579.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.config","doc":"Optional configuration option for tactics "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L177-L177","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.locationWildcard","link":"./../semantic/8686668078641602253.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.locationWildcard","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L178-L178","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.locationHyp","link":"./../semantic/17459380237696960367.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.locationHyp","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L179-L179","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.location","link":"./../semantic/9029872655426014641.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.location","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L181-L181","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.change","link":"./../semantic/13365348163290232413.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.change","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L182-L182","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.changeWith","link":"./../semantic/1495550040230082957.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.changeWith","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L184-L184","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.rwRule","link":"./../semantic/11754272582006582847.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.rwRule","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L185-L185","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.rwRuleSeq","link":"./../semantic/8614910667382302993.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.rwRuleSeq","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L187-L194","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.rewriteSeq","link":"./../semantic/7034096591346696073.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.rewriteSeq","doc":"`rewrite [e]` applies identity `e` as a rewrite rule to the target of the main goal.\nIf `e` is preceded by left arrow (`←` or `<-`), the rewrite is applied in the reverse direction.\nIf `e` is a defined constant, then the equational theorems associated with `e` are used. This provides a convenient way to unfold `e`.\n- `rewrite [e₁, ..., eₙ]` applies the given rules sequentially.\n- `rewrite [e] at l` rewrites `e` at location(s) `l`, where `l` is either `*` or a list of hypotheses in the local context. In the latter case, a turnstile `⊢` or `|-` can also be used, to signify the target of the goal.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L196-L199","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.rwSeq","link":"./../semantic/942419933796965745.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.rwSeq","doc":"`rw` is like `rewrite`, but also tries to close the goal by \"cheap\" (reducible) `rfl` afterwards.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L201-L208","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.rwWithRfl","link":"./../semantic/4895799779413866473.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.rwWithRfl","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L210-L211","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.expandRwSeq","link":"./../semantic/16999968994958819823.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.expandRwSeq","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L213-L222","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.injection","link":"./../semantic/15378904982438114237.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.injection","doc":"The `injection` tactic is based on the fact that constructors of inductive data types are injections.\nThat means that if `c` is a constructor of an inductive datatype, and if `(c t₁)` and `(c t₂)` are two terms that are equal then  `t₁` and `t₂` are equal too.\nIf `q` is a proof of a statement of conclusion `t₁ = t₂`, then injection applies injectivity to derive the equality of all arguments of `t₁` and `t₂`\nplaced in the same positions. For example, from `(a::b) = (c::d)` we derive `a=c` and `b=d`. To use this tactic `t₁` and `t₂`\nshould be constructor applications of the same constructor.\nGiven `h : a::b = c::d`, the tactic `injection h` adds two new hypothesis with types `a = c` and `b = d` to the main goal.\nThe tactic `injection h with h₁ h₂` uses the names `h₁` and `h₂` to name the new hypotheses.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L224-L224","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.injections","link":"./../semantic/9338558358198475331.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.injections","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L226-L226","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.discharger","link":"./../semantic/15784591185070654703.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.discharger","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L228-L228","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.simpPre","link":"./../semantic/7060007119749291109.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.simpPre","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L229-L229","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.simpPost","link":"./../semantic/14152649603224711761.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.simpPost","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L230-L230","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.simpLemma","link":"./../semantic/11186679164186505719.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.simpLemma","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L231-L231","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.simpErase","link":"./../semantic/15279754266353709603.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.simpErase","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L232-L232","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.simpStar","link":"./../semantic/7604022633638082099.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.simpStar","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L233-L244","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.simp","link":"./../semantic/5118178029511841149.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.simp","doc":"The `simp` tactic uses lemmas and hypotheses to simplify the main goal target or non-dependent hypotheses. It has many variants.\n- `simp` simplifies the main goal target using lemmas tagged with the attribute `[simp]`.\n- `simp [h₁, h₂, ..., hₙ]` simplifies the main goal target using the lemmas tagged with the attribute `[simp]` and the given `hᵢ`'s, where the `hᵢ`'s are expressions. If an `hᵢ` is a defined constant `f`, then the equational lemmas associated with `f` are used. This provides a convenient way to unfold `f`.\n- `simp [*]` simplifies the main goal target using the lemmas tagged with the attribute `[simp]` and all hypotheses.\n- `simp only [h₁, h₂, ..., hₙ]` is like `simp [h₁, h₂, ..., hₙ]` but does not use `[simp]` lemmas\n- `simp [-id₁, ..., -idₙ]` simplifies the main goal target using the lemmas tagged with the attribute `[simp]`, but removes the ones named `idᵢ`.\n- `simp at h₁ h₂ ... hₙ` simplifies the hypotheses `h₁ : T₁` ... `hₙ : Tₙ`. If the target or another hypothesis depends on `hᵢ`, a new simplified hypothesis `hᵢ` is introduced, but the old one remains in the local context.\n- `simp at *` simplifies all the hypotheses and the target.\n- `simp [*] at *` simplifies target and all (propositional) hypotheses using the other hypotheses.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L245-L250","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.simpAll","link":"./../semantic/1777980890631261269.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.simpAll","doc":"`simp_all` is a stronger version of `simp [*] at *` where the hypotheses and target are simplified\nmultiple times until no simplication is applicable.\nOnly non-dependent propositional hypotheses are considered.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L252-L256","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.dsimp","link":"./../semantic/505461173764929039.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.dsimp","doc":"The `dsimp` tactic is the definitional simplifier. It is similar to `simp` but only applies theorems that hold by\nreflexivity. Thus, the result is guaranteed to be definitionally equal to the input.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L258-L261","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.delta","link":"./../semantic/8404102376702625875.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.delta","doc":"`delta id` delta-expands the definition `id`.\n  This is a low-level tactic, it will expose how recursive definitions have been compiled by Lean. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L262-L266","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.unfold","link":"./../semantic/5921869961066811635.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.unfold","doc":"`unfold id,+` unfolds definition `id`. For non-recursive definitions, this tactic is identical to `delta`.\n  For recursive definitions, it hides the encoding tricks used by the Lean frontend to convince the\n  kernel that the definition terminates. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L270-L270","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticRefine_lift_","link":"./../semantic/6391212576157367071.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticRefine_lift_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L272-L278","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticHave_","link":"./../semantic/5943497921772062149.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticHave_","doc":"`have h : t := e` adds the hypothesis `h : t` to the current goal if `e` a term of type `t`. If `t` is omitted, it will be inferred.\nIf `h` is omitted, the name `this` is used.\nThe variant `have pattern := e` is equivalent to `match e with | pattern => _`, and it is convenient for types that have only applicable constructor.\nExample: given `h : p ∧ q ∧ r`, `have ⟨h₁, h₂, h₃⟩ := h` produces the hypotheses `h₁ : p`, `h₂ : q`, and `h₃ : r`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L280-L283","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tacticHave__:=_»","link":"./../semantic/12352114813347208607.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tacticHave__:=_»","doc":"`have h := e` adds the hypothesis `h : t` if `e : t`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L284-L291","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticSuffices_","link":"./../semantic/17216286269840812715.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticSuffices_","doc":"Given a main goal `ctx |- t`, `suffices h : t' from e` replaces the main goal with `ctx |- t'`,\n`e` must have type `t` in the context `ctx, h : t'`.\n\nThe variant `suffices h : t' by tac` is a shorthand for `suffices h : t' from by tac`.\nIf `h :` is omitted, the name `this` is used.\n "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L292-L298","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticLet_","link":"./../semantic/11036141416581060819.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticLet_","doc":"`let h : t := e` adds the hypothesis `h : t := e` to the current goal if `e` a term of type `t`.\nIf `t` is omitted, it will be inferred.\nThe variant `let pattern := e` is equivalent to `match e with | pattern => _`, and it is convenient for types that have only applicable constructor.\nExample: given `h : p ∧ q ∧ r`, `let ⟨h₁, h₂, h₃⟩ := h` produces the hypotheses `h₁ : p`, `h₂ : q`, and `h₃ : r`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L299-L303","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticShow_","link":"./../semantic/16904415371445161375.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticShow_","doc":"`show t` finds the first goal whose target unifies with `t`. It makes that the main goal,\n performs the unification, and replaces the target with the unified version of `t`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L304-L304","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.letrec","link":"./../semantic/13288614185253177717.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.letrec","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L309-L309","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticRefine_lift'_","link":"./../semantic/7981488426011560985.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticRefine_lift'_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L310-L310","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticHave'_","link":"./../semantic/9560706010160320079.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticHave'_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L311-L311","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tacticHave'__:=_»","link":"./../semantic/4468879659201609181.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tacticHave'__:=_»","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L312-L312","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticLet'_","link":"./../semantic/10094013893245795857.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticLet'_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L314-L314","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.inductionAlt","link":"./../semantic/2879377407752611243.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.inductionAlt","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L315-L315","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.inductionAlts","link":"./../semantic/2380395907437552519.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.inductionAlts","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L316-L330","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.induction","link":"./../semantic/5069327674316859865.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.induction","doc":"Assuming `x` is a variable in the local context with an inductive type, `induction x` applies induction on `x` to the main goal,\nproducing one goal for each constructor of the inductive type, in which the target is replaced by a general instance of that constructor\nand an inductive hypothesis is added for each recursive argument to the constructor.\nIf the type of an element in the local context depends on `x`, that element is reverted and reintroduced afterward,\nso that the inductive hypothesis incorporates that hypothesis as well.\nFor example, given `n : Nat` and a goal with a hypothesis `h : P n` and target `Q n`, `induction n` produces one goal\nwith hypothesis `h : P 0` and target `Q 0`, and one goal with hypotheses `h : P (Nat.succ a)` and `ih₁ : P a → Q a` and target `Q (Nat.succ a)`.\nHere the names `a` and `ih₁` are chosen automatically and are not accessible. You can use `with` to provide the variables names for each constructor.\n- `induction e`, where `e` is an expression instead of a variable, generalizes `e` in the goal, and then performs induction on the resulting variable.\n- `induction e using r` allows the user to specify the principle of induction that should be used. Here `r` should be a theorem whose result type must be of the form `C t`, where `C` is a bound variable and `t` is a (possibly empty) sequence of bound variables\n- `induction e generalizing z₁ ... zₙ`, where `z₁ ... zₙ` are variables in the local context, generalizes over `z₁ ... zₙ` before applying the induction but then introduces them in each goal. In other words, the net effect is that each inductive hypothesis is generalized.\n- Given `x : Nat`, `induction x with | zero => tac₁ | succ x' ih => tac₂` uses tactic `tac₁` for the `zero` case, and `tac₂` for the `succ` case.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L332-L332","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.generalizeArg","link":"./../semantic/12275713363721179263.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.generalizeArg","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L333-L336","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.generalize","link":"./../semantic/6653091198570054015.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.generalize","doc":"`generalize ([h :] e = x),+` replaces all occurrences `e`s in the main goal with a fresh hypothesis `x`s.\nIf `h` is given, `h : e = x` is introduced as well. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L338-L338","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.casesTarget","link":"./../semantic/16675780732658232935.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.casesTarget","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L339-L350","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.cases","link":"./../semantic/6241084935010701159.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.cases","doc":"Assuming `x` is a variable in the local context with an inductive type, `cases x` splits the main goal,\nproducing one goal for each constructor of the inductive type, in which the target is replaced by a general instance of that constructor.\nIf the type of an element in the local context depends on `x`, that element is reverted and reintroduced afterward,\nso that the case split affects that hypothesis as well. `cases` detects unreachable cases and closes them automatically.\nFor example, given `n : Nat` and a goal with a hypothesis `h : P n` and target `Q n`, `cases n` produces one goal with hypothesis `h : P 0` and target `Q 0`,\nand one goal with hypothesis `h : P (Nat.succ a)` and target `Q (Nat.succ a)`. Here the name `a` is chosen automatically and are not accessible. You can use `with` to provide the variables names for each constructor.\n- `cases e`, where `e` is an expression instead of a variable, generalizes `e` in the goal, and then cases on the resulting variable.\n- Given `as : List α`, `cases as with | nil => tac₁ | cons a as' => tac₂`, uses tactic `tac₁` for the `nil` case, and `tac₂` for the `cons` case, and `a` and `as'` are used as names for the new variables introduced.\n- `cases h : e`, where `e` is a variable or an expression, performs cases on `e` as above, but also adds a hypothesis `h : e = ...` to each hypothesis, where `...` is the constructor instance for that particular case.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L352-L353","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.renameI","link":"./../semantic/828759459020954065.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.renameI","doc":"`rename_i x_1 ... x_n` renames the last `n` inaccessible names using the given names. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L355-L359","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticRepeat_","link":"./../semantic/3072633779721027895.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticRepeat_","doc":"`repeat tac` applies `tac` to main goal. If the application succeeds,\nthe tactic is applied recursively to the generated subgoals until it eventually fails.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L363-L370","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticTrivial","link":"./../semantic/158243492662253515.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticTrivial","doc":"`trivial` tries different simple tactics (e.g., `rfl`, `contradiction`, ...) to close the current goal.\nYou can use the command `macro_rules` to extend the set of tactics used. Example:\n```\nmacro_rules | `(tactic| trivial) => `(tactic| simp)\n```\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L372-L376","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.split","link":"./../semantic/16218723192580453945.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.split","doc":"The `split` tactic is useful for breaking nested if-then-else and match expressions in cases.\nFor a `match` expression with `n` cases, the `split` tactic generates at most `n` subgoals\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L378-L378","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.dbgTrace","link":"./../semantic/5565642550997402987.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.dbgTrace","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L380-L382","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticStop_","link":"./../semantic/15071623451722924603.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticStop_","doc":"`stop` is a helper tactic for \"discarding\" the rest of a proof. It is useful when working on the middle of a complex proofs,\n    and less messy than commenting the remainder of the proof. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L384-L390","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.specialize","link":"./../semantic/11494927290347710701.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.specialize","doc":"The tactic `specialize h a₁ ... aₙ` works on local hypothesis `h`.\nThe premises of this hypothesis, either universal quantifications or non-dependent implications,\nare instantiated by concrete terms coming either from arguments `a₁` ... `aₙ`.\nThe tactic adds a new hypothesis with the same name `h := h a₁ ... aₙ` and tries to clear the previous one.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L399-L399","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticUnhygienic_","link":"./../semantic/2869729097448656875.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.tacticUnhygienic_","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L401-L402","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.fail","link":"./../semantic/422014296507218463.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.fail","doc":"`fail msg` is a tactic that always fail and produces an error using the given message. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L404-L404","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.checkpoint","link":"./../semantic/9423461967644818309.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.checkpoint","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L406-L406","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.save","link":"./../semantic/1661715914132767849.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.save","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L408-L409","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.sleep","link":"./../semantic/15696640080925703835.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.sleep","doc":"The tactic `sleep ms` sleeps for `ms` milliseconds and does nothing. It is used for debugging purposes only. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L411-L413","name":"Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tacticExists_,,»","link":"./../semantic/10911497228878991119.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Tactic.«tacticExists_,,»","doc":"`exists e₁, e₂, ...` is shorthand for `refine ⟨e₁, e₂, ...⟩; try trivial`. It is useful for existential goals. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L419-L419","name":"Lean.Parser.Attr.simp","link":"./../semantic/1282294142236588413.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#Lean.Parser.Attr.simp","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/56cd6c1ff519d8be39f35875b5bf8719e6101c20/src/Init/Tactics.lean#L425-L428","name":"«term‹_›»","link":"./../semantic/15895982054014726951.xml#","docLink":"./Init/Tactics.html#«term‹_›»","doc":"`‹t›` resolves to an (arbitrary) hypothesis of type `t`. It is useful for referring to hypotheses without accessible names.\n`t` may contain holes that are solved by unification with the expected type; in particular, `‹_›` is a shortcut for `by assumption`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L9-L9","name":"LeanColls.UninitPointed","link":"./../semantic/2677583548126826849.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.UninitPointed","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L11-L11","name":"LeanColls.Uninit","link":"./../semantic/15873147024975890181.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L15-L15","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.instNonemptyUninit","link":"./../semantic/16068147251798855403.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.instNonemptyUninit","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L17-L17","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.uninitUnsafe","link":"./../semantic/8892764762206569941.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.uninitUnsafe","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L19-L19","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.uninit","link":"./../semantic/1188590019717671521.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.uninit","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L21-L21","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.initUnsafe","link":"./../semantic/5265311148064787995.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.initUnsafe","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L23-L23","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.init","link":"./../semantic/414933903019088095.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.init","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L25-L25","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.instInhabitedUninit","link":"./../semantic/14331513770433595569.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.instInhabitedUninit","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L27-L27","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.getValue?","link":"./../semantic/15818769652958864123.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.getValue?","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L29-L31","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.ofOption","link":"./../semantic/8291082913222697383.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.ofOption","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L33-L33","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.getValue_ofOption","link":"./../semantic/14893575488901226565.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.getValue_ofOption","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L34-L34","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.ofOption_getValue","link":"./../semantic/13919571141528388653.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.ofOption_getValue","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L36-L38","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.getValue?_init","link":"./../semantic/9821731530410929217.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.getValue?_init","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L40-L42","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.getValue?_uninit","link":"./../semantic/16479470355701454873.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.getValue?_uninit","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b531806eb5a04c0/LeanColls/Uninit.lean#L44-L44","name":"LeanColls.Uninit.isInit","link":"./../semantic/11254048231580561031.xml#","docLink":"./LeanColls/Uninit.html#LeanColls.Uninit.isInit","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/JamesGallicchio/LeanColls/blob/b65b69f41b42ee9a8c1ae4fd3b53